==English==

===Adverb===
'''momentarily'''
# for a [[moment]] or [[instant]]
# in a moment or very [[soon]]; [[at any moment]].
# [[progressively]], or moment by moment

=== Usage note ===
While the term ''momentarily'' is commonly used to mean "in a moment", there are people who feel it should only be used to mean "for a moment," and the former usage may be subjected to correction in a formal or academic setting.